  <div class="card-header bg-transparent border-dark" ><h5>ABOUT RELIANCE</h5></div>
  <div class="card-body text-dark">
  
  <p class="card-text">Reliance Industries Limited also known as RIL is India's biggest private division endeavor. After the government Controlled Indian Oil Corporation, Reliance Industries became the second largest company in India on the grounds of market capitalization and revenue. Thus this organization is the dream company for a lot of engineering graduates. The company was first founded in 1977 by Dhirubhai Ambani and is now headed by Mukesh Ambani with its headquarters in Mumbai. Therefore the Reliance Recruitment Process has an importance in itself.
  </p>
    
     <p class="card-text">Reliance Industries holds the record for the highest revenue in the private sector and are responsible for around 5% of the country's total revenues which consists of only custom and excise duty.
         Apart from the company's core businesses which include petrochemical, refining, natural resources, oil and gas, Reliance Industries also hire for textiles, retail business, telecommunications and SEZ development (Special Economic Zone).</p>
        <p class="card-text"><b> Why RIL?</b>
<br>Reliance Industries is a well-established company not just in India but it is spread worldwide thereby increasing the increasing the job opportunities for aspirants. This year Reliance Jio Infocom Ltd has hired 5,31,250 freshers with an average package of Rs 3.75 F + 15% V + LB.

         
     
     <h5 class="card-title">Reliance Recruitment Process -Eligibility Criteria :</h5>
    <p class="card-text">•	Min 60% in 10th and 12th
<br>•	60 percent/ 6.5 CGPA or above in B.E./B.Tech.
<br>•	Year Gap of not more than 1 year.
<br>•	There should not be any active backlogs
<br>•	Degree in any of the mentioned engineering subjects. -
<br>•	B.Tech - Computer Science & Engineering
<br>•	B.Tech - Computer Science & Engineering with Bioinformatics
<br>•	B.Tech - Information Technology
<br>•	B.Tech - Chemical Engineering
<br>•	B.Tech - Mechanical Engineering
<br>•	B.Tech - Electrical & Electronics Engineering
<br>•	B.Tech - Electronics & Communication Engineering
<br>•	B.Tech - Electronics & Instrumentation Engineering
    

    <h5 class="card-title">Reliance Recruitment Process - Job Role and CTC:</h5>
      <p class="card-text">GET (Graduate Engineer Trainee)	5.85LPA
<br>Process engineer	7.09LPA
<br>IT Associate	3.5LPA
      

     <h5 class="card-title">Reliance Selection Process-</h5>
           <p class="card-text">To Hire the eligible candidates, Reliance Industries are going to conduct the Reliance Selection Process. Basically, the Reliance Selection Rounds consists of 3 rounds. And they are as following:</p>
<br>•	Written Exam
<br>•	Technical Interview
<br>•	HR Interview
           
           
      
      <h5 class="card-title">Reliance Test Pattern  -</h5>
     <p class="card-text">The aptitude section consists of 30 questions and the technical section consists of 30 questions. So candidates must complete all the 60 questions in 60 minutes.</p>
<br>Section	<br>No of questions	<br>Time Duration
<br>Aptitude (Quants + Reasoning + Verbal)	30	30 mins
<br>Technical	30	30 mins
<br>Total	60	60 mins
     
     
